  "antony2023|richardson2011": "SOURCE 1: Antony (2022). Antony's 2022 discussion paper argues that resilience may be supported across nested environmental layers; it is a conceptual application, not an empirical demonstration that resilience can be taught. Evidence type: Discussion paper using Bronfenbrenner's theory. Evidence limit: No empirical sample; the paper reviews ideas and implications for childhood resilience. It argues that resilience may be supported or taught across nested settings; it does not empirically demonstrate that an intervention taught resilience. SOURCE 2: Richardson (2011). Richardson's metatheory maps disruption and several possible forms of reintegration; it is a conceptual model, not evidence that every hard period moves toward growth. Evidence type: Conceptual metatheory article. Evidence limit: No student intervention sample; the article applies a metatheory to rehabilitation and medicine. It maps several possible forms of reintegration and does not show that disruption necessarily causes growth or follows one sequence for every person. Comparison question: what becomes visible when Context, Culture & Social Ecology is placed beside Resilience as Process, and which link is a course interpretation rather than a source finding? Keep the methods separate: this comparison helps you reason across sources; it does not mean either source tested, confirmed, or caused the other source's claim.",
