  "jadmiko2024|yeager2019": "SOURCE 1: Jadmiko, Mustika, and Bashiruddin (2024). Reflective-writing and resilience scores increased after the workshops in this 57-student one-group study; the design does not establish causation. Evidence type: One-group pre-test and post-test study. Evidence limit: 57 nursing students who completed reflective-writing workshops. Scores were higher after the workshops, but without a comparison group the study cannot isolate the workshop as the cause or establish generalizability. SOURCE 2: Yeager and colleagues (2019). A brief intervention produced a small GPA benefit for lower-achieving ninth-grade students and increased advanced-mathematics enrolment overall in this United States sample; the grade effect depended on school peer norms. Evidence type: Individually randomized national field experiment. Evidence limit: 12,490 ninth-grade students in 65 regular United States public high schools. The effects were small and context-dependent; the study supports claims about this brief intervention and population, not every learner or mindset message. Comparison question: what becomes visible when Reflection & Metacognition and Resilience as Process is placed beside Mindset & Beliefs About Ability and Context, Culture & Social Ecology, and which link is a course interpretation rather than a source finding? Keep the methods separate: this comparison helps you reason across sources; it does not mean either source tested, confirmed, or caused the other source's claim.",
