   "abstract": "Ungar argues that because resilience occurs even when risk factors are plentiful, far more weight should fall on the role that social and physical ecologies play in positive development under stress, rather than on individual traits. He sets out four principles for an ecological reading of resilience, decentrality, complexity, atypicality, and cultural relativity, and uses them to define resilience in terms of its environmental antecedents. The aim is a framework that can guide theory, research, and the design of interventions for people in environments that block resilience promoting processes.",
