   "abstract": "Ungar reviews how factors linked to resilience interact with a person's social ecology after exposure to traumatic events, organizing the relationship into three principles. Resilience is more a quality of the environment and its capacity to support growth than an individual construct (nurture trumps nature); it looks both similar and different within and between populations (differential impact); and the effect of any one factor varies with the level of risk and shows cultural specificity (cultural variation). He defines resilience as depending on environments that let individuals navigate and negotiate for the resources they need, and notes it can appear as prosocial behaviour or as pathological adaptation depending on the environment.",
